The paper deals with decision-making in uncertain environments, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of spatiotemporal data also suggests a potential connection to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a new framework for modeling uncertainty, which could be of interest to researchers in machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY).
